The data were best described by a model in which P-gp reduced the transfer clearance from plasma to the brain compartments (i.e. influx hindrance) and increased the transfer clearance from the brain compartments to plasma (i.e. efflux enhancement). The transfer clearances between plasma and the different brain compartments that could be assigned to P-gp were incorporated into the model as previously described by Syvänen et al. [51]:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
